Abducted Rev. Fr. Udo Peter of St Patrick’s Catholic Church, Uromi and Rev. Fr. Philemon Oboh of St Joseph Retreat Centre, Ugboha in Edo State have regained freedom. The clerics seized by kidnappers on July 2 were rescued on Wednesday morning and moved to Government House, Benin where Acting Governor Philip Shaibu received them.   Fed Govt: petrol scarcity will linger until full…     Ekweremadu: Court orders AGF to transmit Ukpo’s biodata to…     Buhari: Barkindo was a national asset   Shaibu’s Chief Press Secretary, Musa Ebomhiana, disclosed that the rescue was carried out by a joint security force without the payment of ransom. Ebomhiana stated that his boss hailed the security operatives for rescuing the priests, while urging them to keep up the good job of ridding the State of criminals.